'''Juan Fernando Quintero Paniagua''', better known as '''Juanfer Quintero''' (born 18 January 1993), is a Colombian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as [[midfielder|attacking midfielder]] or [[midfielder|winger]] for [[Argentine Primera División]] club [[Club Atlético River Plate|River Plate]] and the [[Colombia national football team|Colombia national team]].

Quintero first received attention at age 19 due to his performances in the [[2013 South American Youth Championship]], where Colombia won the title. He was named the tournament's MVP with five goals and four assists; shortly after he was recognized as one of the most promising youth prospects in South America and the world.{{refn|<ref>The Times, Sport, 6 October 2012, p. 11</ref><ref name=autogenerated1>{{cite news |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/south-america-under-20s-championship-preview-1531155 |title=South America Under-20s Championship preview by Euan Marshall: Will we find the new Lionel Messi? - Euan Marshall - Mirror Online |publisher=Mirror.co.uk |date=12 January 2013 |access-date=29 June 2013 |archive-date=18 February 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130218171644/http://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/south-america-under-20s-championship-preview-1531155 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="Bleacher Report">{{cite news |url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/1490207-manchester-united-transfer-rumours-juan-fernando-quintero-linked-with-a-move |title=Manchester United Transfer Rumours: Juan Fernando Quintero Linked with a Move |publisher=Bleacher Report |date=18 January 2013 |access-date=29 June 2013 |archive-date=20 March 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130320152314/http://bleacherreport.com/articles/1490207-manchester-united-transfer-rumours-juan-fernando-quintero-linked-with-a-move |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.diariodelhuila.com/site/index.php/menu-deportes/30923-juan-fernando-quintero-revoluciona-el-mercado-europeo |title=Juan Fernando Quintero revoluciona el mercado europeo |publisher=Diariodelhuila.com |access-date=29 June 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130306102913/http://www.diariodelhuila.com/site/index.php/menu-deportes/30923-juan-fernando-quintero-revoluciona-el-mercado-europeo |archive-date=6 March 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://english.gazzetta.it/Football/16-01-2013/quintero-strama-m-inter-ested--manchester-united-like-italy-913862179369.shtml |title=Quintero: "Strama, I'm Inter-ested, Manchester United? I like Italy" - Football - La Gazzetta dello Sport |publisher=English.gazzetta.it |date=17 January 2013 |access-date=29 June 2013 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131202233351/http://english.gazzetta.it/Football/16-01-2013/quintero-strama-m-inter-ested--manchester-united-like-italy-913862179369.shtml |archive-date=2 December 2013 }}</ref>}}{{refn|<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.vanguardia.com/deportes/seleccion-colombia/194465-juan-fernando-quintero-el-mas-goleador |title=Juan Fernando Quintero, el más goleador &#124; Selección Colombia |publisher=Vanguardia.com |access-date=29 June 2013 |archive-date=21 February 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130221050133/http://www.vanguardia.com/deportes/seleccion-colombia/194465-juan-fernando-quintero-el-mas-goleador |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://es.fifa.com/u20worldcup/news/newsid=2000758/index.html?intcmp=newsreader_news_box_1 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20130216011728/http://es.fifa.com/u20worldcup/news/newsid=2000758/index.html?intcmp=newsreader_news_box_1 |url-status=dead |archive-date=16 February 2013 |title=Colombia celebra su tercer título (2-1) |publisher=fifa.com |access-date=29 June 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.calcionews24.com/esclusiva-ag-fifa-spada-sudamericano-sub-20-ecco-chi-sono-i-ventidue-campioni-della-colombia-298312.html |title=Esclusiva, ag. FIFA Spada: "Sudamericano sub 20, ecco chi sono i ventidue campioni della Colombia" &#124; Calcio News 24 |publisher=Calcionews24.com |date=14 October 2011 |access-date=29 June 2013}}</ref><ref name="losandes1">{{cite news |date=27 April 2013 |title=Juan Quintero fue el mejor jugador del torneo |publisher=Losandes.com.ar |url=http://www.losandes.com.ar/notas/2013/2/5/juan-quintero-mejor-jugador-torneo.-695051.asp |url-status=dead |access-date=29 June 2013 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20130403154719/http://www.losandes.com.ar/notas/2013/2/5/juan-quintero-mejor-jugador-torneo.-695051.asp |archive-date=3 April 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://es.fifa.com/u20worldcup/news/newsid=2010405/index.html?intcmp=newsreader_news_box_3 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20130409154211/http://es.fifa.com/u20worldcup/news/newsid=2010405/index.html?intcmp=newsreader_news_box_3 |url-status=dead |archive-date=9 April 2013 |title=Quintero, estrella por aclamación popular |publisher=fifa.com |access-date=29 June 2013}}</ref>}}

After beginning his career in Colombia with [[Envigado Fútbol Club|Envigado]] and [[Atlético Nacional]], Quintero moved to Europe with [[Delfino Pescara 1936|Pescara]] in 2012 and [[FC Porto|Porto]] in 2013, where he won the [[2013 Supertaça Cândido de Oliveira|Supertaça Cândido de Oliveira]] in 2013. He later spent loan spells with [[Stade Rennais FC|Rennes]] in France and [[Independiente Medellín]] in Colombia. In 2017, he joined [[Club Atlético River Plate|River Plate]], initially on loan and then permanently, winning the [[2017 Supercopa Argentina|Supercopa Argentina]] in 2017, the [[2018 Copa Libertadores|Copa Libertadores]] in 2018—scoring a decisive extra-time goal in the final against [[Boca Juniors]]—and the [[Copa Argentina]] in 2019. He moved to China with [[Shenzhen F.C.|Shenzhen FC]] in 2021, before returning to River in 2022. In 2023, he signed for [[Atlético Junior]] and later moved to [[Racing Club de Avellaneda|Racing Club]], winning the [[2024 Copa Sudamericana|Copa Sudamericana]] in 2024. In 2025, he joined [[América de Cali]] before returning once again to River Plate.

At youth level, Quintero won the [[2013 South American Youth Championship|South American Youth Championship]] in 2013, where he was named Most Valuable Player, and also took part in the [[2013 FIFA U-20 World Cup|2013 U-20 World Cup]], where he gained more praise for his talents after making a huge impact in the tournament.<ref name="fifa.com">{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/news/newsid=2132031/index.html?intcmp=newsreader_news_box_1|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131005105321/http://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/news/newsid=2132031/index.html?intcmp=newsreader_news_box_1|url-status=dead|archive-date=5 October 2013|title=Future bright for crestfallen Quintero|last=FIFA.com|date=4 July 2013}}</ref><ref name="ReferenceA">{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/news/newsid=2134375/index.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130713134800/http://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/news/newsid=2134375/index.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=13 July 2013|title=Turkyilmaz: Swiss star, Turkish heart|last=FIFA.com|date=10 July 2013}}</ref> He made his senior debut for the [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]] in 2012 and went on to represent Colombia in the [[2014 FIFA World Cup|2014 World Cup]], where he scored his first world cup goal against [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast]]. In the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] he scored against Japan, becoming the first Colombian to score in two FIFA World Cup competitions. He later featured at the [[2024 Copa América]], helping Colombia reach the final where they finished as runners-up to [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]].

==Club career==
===Envigado===
Born in [[Medellín]], Colombia, he joined the youth squad for [[Envigado Fútbol Club|Envigado]] after an impressive performance during a youth tournament that took place in Medellin.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lospaisitas.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=199:juan-fernando-quintero-puso-a-envigado-futbol-club-cerca-de-la-permanencia&catid=71:futbol&Itemid=62 |title=El coliseo Ivan de Bedut abrió sus puertas al Ponybaloncesto |editor=Web oficial de la Corporación Deportiva Los Paisitas |language=es |access-date=22 January 2013 |archive-date=24 September 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140924233928/http://www.lospaisitas.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=199:juan-fernando-quintero-puso-a-envigado-futbol-club-cerca-de-la-permanencia&catid=71:futbol&Itemid=62 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Quintero made his professional debut in 2009.

At the end of the 2010 season, Quintero helped Envigado retain their place in the [[2010 Categoría Primera A season|Categoría Primera A]].<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |title=Histórico: Antioquia tendrá cuatro equipos en la A en 2011 |url=https://www.futbolred.com/archivo/documento/CMS-8601760 |access-date=2023-11-06 |website=futbolred.com |language=spanish}}</ref> He scored the only goal of the match in the first leg of the relegation play-offs, a 1–0 victory over [[Deportivo Pasto]] .<ref>{{Cite web |title=Deportivo Pasto vs. Envigado - 12 December 2010 - Soccerway |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2010/12/12/colombia/play-offs-12/deportivo-pasto/envigado-futbol-club/1055909/ |access-date=2023-11-06 |website=int.soccerway.com |archive-date=6 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231106154346/https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2010/12/12/colombia/play-offs-12/deportivo-pasto/envigado-futbol-club/1055909/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In the second play-off match, he suffered an injury, fracturing his tibia and being ruled out for two months;<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=15 December 2010 |title=Juan Quintero, jugador de Envigado, sufrió fractura de tibia |url=https://www.futbolred.com/archivo/documento/CMS-8604920 |access-date=2023-11-06 |website=futbolred.com |language=spanish}}</ref> however, his team won 3–0 on aggregate to secure their spot in the top tier for another season.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Envigado vs. Deportivo Pasto - 15 December 2010 - Soccerway |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2010/12/15/colombia/play-offs-12/envigado-futbol-club/deportivo-pasto/1056473/ |access-date=2023-11-06 |website=int.soccerway.com}}</ref>

===Atlético Nacional===
Quintero joined the ranks of [[Atlético Nacional]] in January 2012.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Semana |date=2012-01-03 |title=Así está la bolsa de jugadores del torneo colombiano |url=https://www.semana.com/asi-esta-bolsa-jugadores-del-torneo-colombiano/251480-3/ |access-date=2023-11-06 |website=Semana.com Últimas Noticias de Colombia y el Mundo |language=spanish |archive-date=6 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231106154345/https://www.semana.com/asi-esta-bolsa-jugadores-del-torneo-colombiano/251480-3/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Loan to Pescara===
In July 2012, Quintero then joined Serie A club [[Pescara Calcio|Pescara]] for a fee of $2 million,<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=17 July 2012 |title=Juan Fernando Quintero es nuevo jugador del Pescara de Italia |url=https://www.futbolred.com/archivo/documento/CMS-12040507 |access-date=2023-11-06 |website=futbolred.com |language=spanish |archive-date=6 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231106154345/https://www.futbolred.com/archivo/documento/CMS-12040507 |url-status=live }}</ref> wasting no time in impressing European scouts.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.antena2.com.co/audios/planeta-futbol/victor-marulanda-reconocio-la-opcion-de-juan--34 |title=Víctor Marulanda reconoció la opción de Juan Fernando Quintero a Italia (Jul-13-12) &#124; Antena 2 - RCN Radio |publisher=Antena 2 |access-date=29 June 2013 |archive-date=28 September 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928125606/http://www.antena2.com.co/audios/planeta-futbol/victor-marulanda-reconocio-la-opcion-de-juan--34 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.futbolred.com/liga-postobon/noticias/pretemporada2012i/doce-refuerzos-no-son-suficientes-nacional-espera-dos-fichajes-mas/10936610 |title=Doce refuerzos no son suficientes: Nacional espera dos fichajes más |editor=Futbolred.com |language=es |access-date=22 January 2013}}</ref> On 23 September 2012, he scored his first goal with the club, a free kick in a 1–1 draw against Bologna.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=2012-09-23 |title=Primer gol de Juan Fernando Quintero en Italia |url=https://www.colombia.com/futbol/colombianos-en-el-exterior/videos/sdi26/46752/primer-gol-de-juan-fernando-quintero-en-italia |access-date=2023-11-06 |website=Colombia.com |language=spanish |archive-date=6 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231106154346/https://www.colombia.com/futbol/colombianos-en-el-exterior/videos/sdi26/46752/primer-gol-de-juan-fernando-quintero-en-italia |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=23 September 2012 |title=Bologna vs. Pescara |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2012/09/23/italy/serie-a/bologna-fc-1909/pescara-calcio/1351283/ |access-date=2023-11-06 |website=int.soccerway.com |archive-date=6 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231106155629/https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2012/09/23/italy/serie-a/bologna-fc-1909/pescara-calcio/1351283/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

It was reported in early 2013 that [[Inter Milan]] and [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]] have confirmed their bidding interest, although Udinese was the only club to have made an official bid.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.fichajes.com/serie-a/inter-de-milan-y-udinese-batallan-por-un-talento-colombiano_56525 |title=Sitio en curso de modificación |publisher=Fichajes.com |access-date=29 June 2013 |archive-date=13 May 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130513041742/http://www.fichajes.com/serie-a/inter-de-milan-y-udinese-batallan-por-un-talento-colombiano_56525 |url-status=live }}</ref>

In early April 2013, it was reported that Quintero suffered an injury and would be out for a month. In mid May 2013, Quintero posted on [[Twitter]] 'goodbye and thank you' to Pescara, hinting that he was to leave in the Italian side in the summer. While Pescara claimed that he has not been 'sold', it hinted Quintero's desire to leave the club overall.
<ref>{{cite news |url=http://forzaitalianfootball.com/2013/05/pescaras-quintero-angers-club-officials-after-twitter-gaffe/ |title=Pescara's Quintero angers club officials after Twitter gaffe |publisher=Forza Italian Football |date=21 May 2013 |access-date=29 June 2013 |archive-date=3 February 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160203030715/http://forzaitalianfootball.com/2013/05/pescaras-quintero-angers-club-officials-after-twitter-gaffe/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.football-italia.net/34418/quintero-infuriates-pescara |title=Quintero infuriates Pescara |publisher=Football Italia |date=20 May 2013 |access-date=29 June 2013}}</ref>

===Porto===
In June 2013, Quintero joined Porto from Pescara for €5 million, with the Italian club retaining 50% of the economic rights.<ref name=Porto>{{cite web|url=http://www.fcporto.pt/Comunicados/FR46001.pdf|title=COMUNICADO |trans-title=Communication|date=13 July 2013|access-date=4 July 2015|publisher=F.C. Porto|language=pt}}</ref> Quintero signed a four-year contract with a release clause of €40 million.<ref name=Porto/> By joining Porto, he linked up with fellow countryman [[Jackson Martínez]].

Quintero made his first full debut appearance in the [[2013 Emirates Cup]] against [[SSC Napoli|Napoli]]. He assisted Porto's first goal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ksAswQCaU_w|title=YouTube|website=www.youtube.com|access-date=9 November 2013|archive-date=11 May 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140511060542/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ksAswQCaU_w&app=desktop|url-status=live}}</ref>

====2013–14 season====
[[File:Juan Fernando Quintero.jpg|thumb|120px|Quintero training with [[FC Porto|Porto]] in 2014]]
Quintero's first official match with Porto was in the [[2013 Supertaça Cândido de Oliveira]], where he came on as a sub after 76 minutes with Porto winning 3–0. Porto went on to win the match, thus giving Quintero's very first silverware not only in Europe, but in his club career.<ref name="1stwin">{{cite web|title=FC Porto 3-0 V. Guimarães |url=http://www.record.xl.pt/emdireto/?id_game=69407&id_post=1778048 |publisher=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]] |language=pt |date=10 August 2013 |access-date=7 September 2013 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130914170432/http://www.record.xl.pt/emdireto/?id_game=69407&id_post=1778048 |archive-date=14 September 2013}}</ref>

Quintero debuted in his first league match for the club against [[Vitória F.C.|Vitória de Setúbal]], coming on as a sub and scoring less than a minute later.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F1l6wDPJHLk|title=YouTube|website=youtube.com|access-date=9 November 2013|archive-date=1 July 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150701061220/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F1l6wDPJHLk|url-status=live}}</ref> Quintero provided his first assist for the club two weeks later against [[F.C. Paços de Ferreira|Pacos Ferreira]] in a 1–0 victory.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BfsRInfDQ6s|title=Liga Portuguesa 13/14 (3ªJ): P. Ferreira 0-1 FC Porto (01-09-2013)|last=FC Porto|date=2 September 2013|via=YouTube|access-date=9 November 2013|archive-date=31 October 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131031144944/http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BfsRInfDQ6s&feature=youtu.be|url-status=live}}</ref> In a match against [[Vitória S.C.|Vitória de Guimarães]], Quintero drew a penalty that was successfully converted, thus granting him an assist in a 1–0 home victory. In a match against [[F.C. Arouca|Arouca]], Quintero came on in the 90th minute and was subsequently fouled near the box. He then converted an impressive free kick goal, just seconds after coming in.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=6 October 2013 |title=Jackson y Quintero ponen líder al Porto en triunfo 3-1 sobre Arouca |url=https://www.futbolred.com/archivo/documento/CMS-13104824 |access-date=2024-12-21 |website=futbolred.com |language=spanish |archive-date=25 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241225234605/https://www.futbolred.com/archivo/documento/CMS-13104824 |url-status=live }}</ref>

In late October, Quintero suffered a hamstring injury, expecting to be out for a month.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://comutricolor.com/juan-fernado-quintero-lesion-porto/|title=Juan Fernando Quintero se lesionó y es duda ante Holanda y Bélgica - ComuTricolor|website=comutricolor.com|access-date=23 October 2013|archive-date=27 October 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131027090257/http://comutricolor.com/juan-fernado-quintero-lesion-porto/|url-status=dead}}</ref> Following his return in December, Quintero requested to play with the B-squad in order to keep his fitness up if he was not able to get guarantee minutes with the A-squad.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Juan Fernando Quintero pide jugar en la B del Porto |url=http://www.lafm.com.co/noticias/juan-fernando-quintero-pide-151830 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.today/20131220013000/http://www.lafm.com.co/noticias/juan-fernando-quintero-pide-151830 |archive-date=20 December 2013 |access-date=20 December 2013 |website=lafm.com |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=19 December 2013 |title=Juan Fernando Quintero pidió jugar en el filial del Porto |url=http://www.elheraldo.co/deportes/juan-fernando-quintero-pidio-jugar-en-el-filial-del-porto-136555 |website=El Heraldo |access-date=20 December 2013 |archive-date=20 December 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131220045736/http://www.elheraldo.co/deportes/juan-fernando-quintero-pidio-jugar-en-el-filial-del-porto-136555 |url-status=live }}</ref>

After a long period of matches spent solely on the bench, or coming on as a late substitute during [[Paulo Fonseca]]'s time as manager, averaging around 20 minutes per game in the league, Quintero found his way back into the team after new manager [[Luís Castro (Portuguese footballer)|Luís Castro]] took over in March 2014. Quintero's next significant performance was against [[SSC Napoli|Napoli]] in the [[2013–14 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]], where he came close to scoring his first goal in European competition, when a Napoli defender's clearance rebounded off his leg and hit the post.

Quintero scored his third goal of the season against [[C.F. Os Belenenses|Belenenses]], coming on as a half time substitute and setting up several opportunities for teammate and fellow countryman [[Jackson Martínez]], but eventually it would be Quintero who decided the game with the only goal in a 1–0 victory.

Quintero made his first 90-minute appearance for Porto on 6 April 2014, in a home match against [[Associação Académica de Coimbra – O.A.F.|Académica]]. He provided somewhat of an assist, again for Jackson Martinez, when he was fouled in the box in the 38th minute, which resulted in a converted Jackson Martínez penalty. Quintero then scored his fourth goal of the season a week later, in the 91st minute in a 3–1 victory over [[S.C. Braga]], after a counterattack which he started.

On 21 April, Quintero came on as a second-half substitute against fellow northerners [[Rio Ave F.C.|Rio Ave]] and made a significant impact to the match.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Porto vs. Rio Ave - 21 April 2014 - Soccerway |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2014/04/21/portugal/portuguese-liga-/futebol-clube-do-porto/rio-ave-fc/1511926/ |access-date=2023-11-02 |website=int.soccerway.com}}</ref> He was involved in all three of the goals, but only got one direct assist. A chipped through ball to Jackson Martinez resulted in him being brought down for a penalty, which Martínez scored. Next, he assisted [[Héctor Herrera]]'s header with a chipped through ball. The third goal of the game came from Porto right back [[Danilo (footballer, born July 1991)|Danilo]], who scored a deflected free kick after Quintero had been fouled just outside the box.

====2014–15 season====
Quintero missed Porto's first league game of the season due to a death in his family, but returned to the Porto squad for the next league match versus [[F.C. Paços de Ferreira|Paços de Ferreira]]. Coming on for the injured [[Cristian Tello]], he provided an assist, yet again for fellow Colombian Jackson Martínez, for the only goal in a 1–0 victory for Porto.

Quintero scored his first goal of the season against [[F.C. Arouca]] from long distance, Porto ended up winning 0–5.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Arouca vs. Porto - 25 October 2014 - Soccerway |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2014/10/25/portugal/portuguese-liga-/fc-arouca/futebol-clube-do-porto/1758027/ |access-date=2023-11-02 |website=int.soccerway.com}}</ref>

On 16 December 2014, Porto purchased the remaining 50% economic rights of Quintero from Pescara for €4.5 million, giving them complete ownership of him.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fcporto.pt/Comunicados/Compra50Quintero16122014.pdf|title=COMUNICADO |trans-title=Communication|date=16 December 2014|access-date=4 July 2015|publisher=F.C. Porto|language=pt}}</ref>

====Loan to Rennes====
====2015–16====
In August 2015, Quintero signed a season-long loan with Ligue 1 side [[Stade Rennais F.C.|Rennes]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Campo |first=Carlo |date=2015-08-31 |title=Juan Quintero joins Rennes on season-long loan from Porto |url=https://www.thescore.com/fran/news/820107 |access-date=2023-11-02 |website=theScore.com |language=en}}</ref> Quintero made his debut against [[OGC Nice|Nice]], coming on as a sub and providing an assist in a 1–4 loss.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ligue1.com/ligue1/article/ben-arfa-and-nice-light-up-french-football.htm|title=Ligue1.com - Ben Arfa and Nice light up French football|website=www.ligue1.com|access-date=25 December 2015|archive-date=26 December 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151226024236/http://www.ligue1.com/ligue1/article/ben-arfa-and-nice-light-up-french-football.htm|url-status=live}}</ref> Quintero would eventually score his first goal for the club in the match against [[SM Caen]], resulting in a 1–1 draw.<ref>{{cite web |last= |first= |date=11 December 2015 |title=Primer gol de Juan Fernando Quintero en Francia: Rennes 1- Caen 1 |url=http://www.futbolred.com/colombianos-exterior/juan-fernando-quintero-marco-su-primer-gol-en-francia+16455829 |website=futbolred.com}}</ref>

Quintero stated in an interview that he intended to return to Porto after his loan ended, despite rumors linking him to a permanent transfer.<ref>{{cite web |last= |first= |date=22 December 2015 |title=Juan Fernando Quintero con intención de volver al Porto |url=http://colombia.as.com/colombia/2015/12/22/futbol/1450824072_618575.html |website=AS Colombia |access-date=25 December 2015 |archive-date=26 December 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151226015137/http://colombia.as.com/colombia/2015/12/22/futbol/1450824072_618575.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

====Loan to Independiente Medellín====
====2016====
On 18 September 2016, Quintero returned to the [[Categoría Primera A|top flight Colombian league]] on loan, joining [[Independiente Medellín]] from Porto on a one-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Heraldo |first=El |date=2016-09-18 |title=Juan Fernando Quintero, presentado como jugador del Medellín |url=https://www.elheraldo.co/deportes/juan-fernando-quintero-presentado-como-jugador-del-medellin-285968 |access-date=2023-11-02 |website=EL HERALDO |language=es}}</ref> On 9 August 2017, his loan was extended through December 2017.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2017-08-09 |title=Quintero se queda en Medellín unos meses más {{!}} Goal.com Colombia |url=https://www.goal.com/es-co/noticias/quintero-y-una-pequena-opcion-de-quedarse-en-medellin/iqdr95rdfu5h1cjsacwlcgilv |access-date=2023-11-02 |website=www.goal.com |language=es-CO}}</ref>

====Loan to River Plate====
On 24 January 2018, Quintero joined Argentine club [[Club Atlético River Plate|River Plate]] on loan for one year and got the number 8.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cariverplate.com.ar/quintero-firmo-su-contrato-en-river|title=Quintero firmó su contrato con River|date=24 January 2018|publisher=[[Club Atlético River Plate|River Plate]]|access-date=24 January 2018|archive-date=20 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180620024615/http://www.cariverplate.com.ar/quintero-firmo-su-contrato-en-river|url-status=live}}</ref> The deal was settled for €300,000 and included a buyout clause of €5 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abola.pt/Nnh/Noticias/Ver/712609|title=Quintero pode render cinco milhões aos dragões|date=24 January 2018|publisher=[[A Bola]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/fc-porto/detalhe/oficial-quintero-emprestado-ao-river-plate.html|title=Oficial: Quintero emprestado ao River Plate|date=24 January 2018|publisher=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]]}}</ref> On 9 December 2018, in the second leg of the [[2018 Copa Libertadores finals]] against rivals [[Boca Juniors]], Quintero scored a goal in extra time from outside the box to put River Plate up 2–1, then assisted [[Pity Martinez]] in the 120th minute to seal the game at 3–1 and earn River Plate their fourth [[Copa Libertadores]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=3 January 2019 |title=Juan Fernando Quintero discusses his River Plate future |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/juan-fernando-quintero-discusses-his-river-plate-future-23519426 |access-date=2023-11-02 |website=OneFootball |language=en}}</ref> He later got a tattoo on his calf for this occasion in January 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Olé |first=Diario Deportivo |date=2019-01-04 |title=Quintero se tatuó la Copa |url=https://www.ole.com.ar/river-plate/juanfer-quintero-tatuaje-river-copa-libertadores-sigue_0_NlcbcHUEJ.html |access-date=2023-11-02 |website=Olé |language=es |archive-date=2 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231102172906/https://www.ole.com.ar/river-plate/juanfer-quintero-tatuaje-river-copa-libertadores-sigue_0_NlcbcHUEJ.html |url-status=live }}</ref> That same month, he announced that he would continue with River for the 2019 season, putting to rest any rumors surrounding a potential move to China, and praising coach [[Marcelo Gallardo]], saying he was "like a father to me".<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=2019-01-02 |title='Gallardo es como un papá para mi' |url=https://www.ole.com.ar/river-plate/juan-fernando-quintero-river-futuro-china_0_yyjUVRA4n.html |access-date=2023-12-01 |website=Olé |language=es}}</ref>

===River Plate===
====2019====
[[Club Atlético River Plate|River Plate]] made the transfer for Quintero for a fee of €3.5 million. After the departure of [[Pity Martinez]] to the [[MLS]], Quintero took the number 10 jersey.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2019-01-03 |title=Juan Fernando Quintero se quedaría con el 10 en River |url=https://colombia.as.com/colombia/2019/01/03/futbol/1546545212_068704.html |access-date=2023-11-02 |website=Diario AS |language=es-co}}</ref> In February 2019, he renewed his contract until June 2022 and included a buyout clause of €30 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cariverplate.com.ar/river-plate-blinda-a-juan-fernando-quintero|title=River Plate blinda a Juan Fernando Quintero|publisher=Club Atlético River Plate|date=26 February 2019|access-date=7 March 2019}}</ref> In August 2019, he was nominated for the [[FIFA Puskás Award#2019|2019 FIFA Puskás Award]] for his goal scored against [[Racing Club de Avellaneda|Racing Club]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fcf.com.co/index.php/2019/08/19/juan-fernando-quintero-nominado-al-premio-puskas/|title=Juan Fernando Quintero nominado al premio Puskas|access-date=19 August 2019|publisher=FCF|archive-date=22 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190822132631/http://fcf.com.co/index.php/2019/08/19/juan-fernando-quintero-nominado-al-premio-puskas/|url-status=dead}}</ref> His goal eventually finished third, behind second place [[Lionel Messi]], and winner [[Dániel Zsóri]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Young |first=Alex |date=2019-09-23 |title=Daniel Zsori wins Fifa Puskas Award over Messi and Quintero |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/lionel-messi-juan-fernando-quintero-daniel-zsori-fifa-puskas-award-a4244371.html |access-date=2023-11-02 |website=Evening Standard |language=en}}</ref>

=== Shenzhen FC===
In late 2020, Quintero signed for [[Chinese Super League]] club [[Shenzhen F.C.|Shenzhen FC]] for a reported fee of €5.9 million. He joined the team on 1 March 2021.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2021-03-01 |title=Soccer-Shenzhen confirm signing of Colombia's Quintero |language=en |work=Reuters |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/soccer-china-idUKXXN2KZ008 |access-date=2023-11-02}}</ref>

=== River Plate ===

==== 2022 ====
On 21 January 2022, Quintero returned to [[Club Atlético River Plate|River Plate]], joining the club permanently and signing a 2-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Juan Fernando Quintero regresa como jugador al River Plate |url=http://www.elnuevosiglo.com.co/deportes/juan-fernando-quintero-regresa-como-jugador-al-river-plate |access-date=2023-11-02 |website=El Nuevo Siglo |language=es-co |archive-date=2 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231102172909/https://www.elnuevosiglo.com.co/deportes/juan-fernando-quintero-regresa-como-jugador-al-river-plate |url-status=live }}</ref>

In October he made international news for pushing a referee and earning a red card in a defeat.{{citation needed|date=April 2026}}

=== Atlético Junior ===
On 13 January 2023, Quintero joined Colombian side [[Atlético Junior|Junior]], on a one-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-01-15 |title=La primera advertencia de Juan Fernando Quintero en su presentación con el Junior de Barranquilla |url=https://www.infobae.com/america/colombia/2023/01/15/la-primera-advertencia-de-juan-fernando-quintero-en-su-presentacion-con-el-junior-de-barranquilla/ |access-date=2023-11-02 |website=infobae |language=es-ES |archive-date=2 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231102172906/https://www.infobae.com/america/colombia/2023/01/15/la-primera-advertencia-de-juan-fernando-quintero-en-su-presentacion-con-el-junior-de-barranquilla/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He would become the highest paid player in the history of Colombian football, earning a €2.3 million annual salary.<ref>{{Cite web |last=archysport |date=2023-01-13 |title=Salary of Juan Fernando Quintero in the Junior |url=https://www.archysport.com/2023/01/salary-of-juan-fernando-quintero-in-the-junior/ |access-date=2023-11-02 |website=Archysport |language=en-US |archive-date=2 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231102172906/https://www.archysport.com/2023/01/salary-of-juan-fernando-quintero-in-the-junior/ |url-status=live }}</ref> A mix of injuries and playing time disagreements with coach [[Hernán Darío Gómez]], led to Quintero rescinding his contract with the Barranquilla club.<ref>{{Cite web |last=García |first=Por Javier |date=2023-07-09 |title=Juan Fernando Quintero y la verdadera razón de su salida del Junior de Barranquilla |url=https://www.infobae.com/colombia/2023/07/09/juan-fernando-quintero-y-la-verdadera-razon-de-su-salida-del-junior-de-barranquilla/ |access-date=2023-11-02 |website=infobae |language=es-ES}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Olé |first=Diario Deportivo |date=2023-07-30 |title=Bomba: Juanfer Quintero a Racing |url=https://www.ole.com.ar/racing/juanfer-quintero-racing-river-junior_0_NgRf5iLcn9.html |access-date=2023-11-02 |website=Olé |language=es |archive-date=2 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231102172906/https://www.ole.com.ar/racing/juanfer-quintero-racing-river-junior_0_NgRf5iLcn9.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

=== Racing ===
On 17 August 2023, Quintero returned to Argentina, joining [[Racing Club de Avellaneda|Racing]] as a free agent on a two-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-11-02 |title=Oficial: Racing presenta a Juan Quintero |url=https://onefootball.com/es/noticias/oficial-racing-presenta-a-juan-quintero-38054363 |access-date=2023-11-02 |website=OneFootball |language=es |archive-date=2 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231102172906/https://onefootball.com/es/noticias/oficial-racing-presenta-a-juan-quintero-38054363 |url-status=live }}</ref> He scored his first goal in a 1–2 victory against [[Club Atlético Tigre|Tigre]], where he also assisted the other goal. On October 31, he shone by scoring two goals against [[Sport Club Corinthians Paulista|Corinthians]], in the semifinals of the [[Copa Sudamericana]], securing his team's qualification for an international final after 32 years.<ref>{{Cite thesis |last=BARROSO FURTADO |first=ENRICO |title=O IMPACTO DA ECONOMIA NO FUTEBOL ARGENTINO EM COMPARAÇÃO AO FUTEBOL BRASILEIRO |publisher=Faculdades Catolicas |url=https://doi.org/10.17771/pucrio.acad.70828}}</ref> In that competition, he was crowned champion after his team defeated [[Cruzeiro Esporte Clube|Cruzeiro]] by 3—1 in the final.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-08-26 |title=Juanfer Quintero, figura: Gol y asistencia en victoria de Racing |url=https://colombia.as.com/futbol/colombianos-por-el-mundo/juanfer-quintero-figura-gol-y-asistencia-en-victoria-de-racing-n/ |access-date=2023-11-02 |website=Diario AS |language=es-co |archive-date=2 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231102172906/https://colombia.as.com/futbol/colombianos-por-el-mundo/juanfer-quintero-figura-gol-y-asistencia-en-victoria-de-racing-n/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

=== América De Cali ===

On 24 January 2025, Quintero returned to Colombia to play for [[América de Cali]]. After Colombian Apertura season was over, Quintero decided to leave the club.

=== River Plate ===

On 17 July 2025, Quintero joined [[Club Atlético River Plate|River Plate]].

==International career==
===Youth===
====2013 South American Youth Championship====
Quintero was called to represent Colombia wearing the number 10 jersey at the [[2013 South American Youth Championship]].<ref name="Bleacher Report"/><ref name="hereisthecity.com">{{cite web |url=http://hereisthecity.com/2013/01/21/nh-manchester-united-target-impresses-at-south-american-u20-cham/ |title=Manchester United target impresses at South American U20 Championship |publisher=Hereisthecity.com |date=21 January 2013 |access-date=29 June 2013 |archive-date=20 February 2013 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20130220071814/http://hereisthecity.com/2013/01/21/nh-manchester-united-target-impresses-at-south-american-u20-cham/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=20 December 2012 |title=Colombia sub-20 espera contar con Juan Fernando Quintero para el Suramericano |url=http://www.caracol.com.co/noticias/deportes/colombia-sub20-espera-contar-con-juan-fernando-quintero-para-el-suramericano/20121220/nota/1814295.aspx |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131005090918/http://www.caracol.com.co/noticias/deportes/colombia-sub20-espera-contar-con-juan-fernando-quintero-para-el-suramericano/20121220/nota/1814295.aspx |archive-date=5 October 2013 |access-date=29 June 2013 |publisher=Caracol.com.co}}</ref> In the first match against Paraguay, he was voted man of the match after an impressive display setting up the 1–0 victory goal. In the match against a powerful Chile team, Quintero scored a penalty although Colombia lost 2–1.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J4Hwj2oelRY |access-date=9 November 2013 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140511063311/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J4Hwj2oelRY |archive-date=11 May 2014 |website=[[YouTube]] |title=YouTube }}</ref> In the match against Bolivia, Quintero assisted four of the six goals in a 6–0 victory.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Bn1WS_dWsg4 |title=Goles de Colombia (6) vs Bolivia (0) – Sudamericano Juvenil Sub 20 |publisher=YouTube |date=15 January 2013 |access-date=29 June 2013 |archive-date=11 May 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140511063150/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Bn1WS_dWsg4 |url-status=live }}</ref> In the final group stage match against Argentina, Colombia had already qualified thus he did not play until the second half where he scored with an amazing 50 yard free kick despite losing the match 2–3.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rtrAfbWENrc |access-date=9 November 2013 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130120071725/http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rtrAfbWENrc |archive-date=20 January 2013 |website=[[YouTube]] |title=GOLAZO DE TIRO LIBRE!! Juan Fernando Quintero Argentina 3 – 2 Colombia Sudamericano Sub 20 17-01-13 – YouTube }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lBkkRIOqSOc |title=Argentina vs Colombia (3–2) Sudamericano Sub 20 2013 |publisher=YouTube |date=17 January 2013 |access-date=29 June 2013 |archive-date=11 May 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140511064030/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lBkkRIOqSOc |url-status=live }}</ref>

In the first match of the final round, Quintero scored again from an impressive distance in a 2–1 victory over Ecuador.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NqRpkq6Eosg |access-date=9 November 2013 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140511062923/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NqRpkq6Eosg |archive-date=11 May 2014 |website=[[YouTube]] |title=YouTube }}</ref> This brought his goal tally to three and his assist tally to four.<ref name="hereisthecity.com"/> Quintero scored with a penalty against Peru in a 1–0 allowing Colombia to qualify for the [[2013 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] in Turkey.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://es.fifa.com/u20worldcup/news/newsid=1996627/index.html?intcmp=newsreader_news_box_1 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131109164240/http://es.fifa.com/u20worldcup/news/newsid=1996627/index.html?intcmp=newsreader_news_box_1 |url-status=dead |archive-date=9 November 2013 |title=Colombia ya es mundialista (1-0) |publisher=Es.fifa.com |access-date=29 June 2013}}</ref> In the final match against Paraguay who were also Colombia's very first opponent in the U20 South American Youth Championships, he scored a goal in a 2–1 victory where Colombia won the Youth Championships in South America for the third time. In total, Quintero had scored 5 goals and assisted 4 making him MVP of the championship for contributing more than any other player in the tournament.<ref name="losandes1"/>

Quintero was set to join the U20 squad again for the [[2013 Toulon Tournament]], but Pescara refused to allow him to his call-up.<ref>{{cite news |author=Miller Pinto Cobos |url=http://www.ligapostobon.com.co/noticias/es-una-lastima-no-estar-en-toulon-juan-f-quin-142609 |title='Es una lástima no estar en Toulon': Juan F. Quintero |publisher=Ligapostobon.com.co |date=20 April 2013 |access-date=29 June 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131109164932/http://www.ligapostobon.com.co/noticias/es-una-lastima-no-estar-en-toulon-juan-f-quin-142609 |archive-date=9 November 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Prior to the U-20 World Cup, Quintero scored with an impressive free kick in a friendly against the U-20 squad of France.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?feature=player_embedded&v=zIbfWbaTAzU |title=YouTube |website=youtube.com |access-date=17 January 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140511063347/https://www.youtube.com/watch?feature=player_embedded&v=zIbfWbaTAzU |archive-date=11 May 2014 |url-status=dead}}</ref>

====2013 U-20 FIFA World Cup====
{{Quote box | width=30% | align=right| quote="It's difficult to judge a player at this age and know if he'll have a great career, but sometimes it's just blindingly obvious when you get to see a future star. Juan Quintero has got something extra and you can already see that, despite his young age."|source=<small>Australian U-20 coach, [[Paul Okon]] praising Quintero following a 1–1 draw against Colombia in the U-20 FIFA World Cup.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/news/newsid=2132031/index.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130707065519/http://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/news/newsid=2132031/index.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=7 July 2013|title=Future bright for crestfallen Quintero|last=FIFA.com|date=4 July 2013}}</ref></small>}}

Quintero played an entertaining opening match performance of the U-20 FIFA World Cup that was held in Turkey. He made impressive shots with his free kicks as well as creating impressive chances. He set up Colombia's goal in the 78th minute where the game ended 1–1.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/matches/round=259235/match=300232808/index.html?intcmp=livecoverage_box_u20worldcup_en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130626060002/http://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/matches/round=259235/match=300232808/index.html?intcmp=livecoverage_box_u20worldcup_en |url-status=dead |archive-date=26 June 2013 |title=FIFA U-20 World Cup: Colombia 1:1 (0:0) Australia – Summary |publisher=FIFA.com |date=20 June 2013 |access-date=29 June 2013}}</ref> In the match against host nation Turkey, Quintero scored a wonderful goal from outside the box (20 yards), winning the game 1–0 and allowing Colombia to top the group.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/matches/round=259235/match=300235570/summary.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130629060752/http://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/matches/round=259235/match=300235570/summary.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=29 June 2013 |title=FIFA U-20 World Cup: Turkey – Colombia |publisher=FIFA.com |access-date=29 June 2013}}</ref> In the last group match against El Salvador, Quintero assisted the first goal and sealed the victory with an amazing 25 yard goal, allowing Colombia to win 3–0 and win the group.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/matches/round=259235/match=300232839/index.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130701021432/http://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/matches/round=259235/match=300232839/index.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=1 July 2013 |title=FIFA U-20 World Cup: El Salvador 0:3 (0:2) Colombia – Summary |publisher=FIFA.com |access-date=29 June 2013}}</ref> Quintero then played in the next match against South Korea, and managed to save Colombia into extra time with an impressive free kick in the last few seconds of full-time. However, Colombia went on to lose on penalties eventually where he scored one in a 7–8 loss.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/matches/round=259233/match=300232820/index.html?intcmp=newsreader_match_box_1|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140709030619/http://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/matches/round=259233/match=300232820/index.html?intcmp=newsreader_match_box_1|url-status=dead|archive-date=9 July 2014|title=FIFA U-20 World Cup Turkey 2013 – Matches – Colombia-Korea Republic |last=FIFA.com|website=FIFA.com}}</ref> Despite Colombia failing to progress, Quintero was praised as the best player in the group stages.<ref name="fcporto.pt">{{cite web |url=http://www.fcporto.pt/English/News/news_eng_footquinterosigns_130713_76142.asp |title=FCPorto |access-date=13 July 2013 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130716185922/http://www.fcporto.pt/English/News/news_eng_footquinterosigns_130713_76142.asp |archive-date=16 July 2013 }}</ref><ref name="ReferenceA"/>

His goal against El Salvador was later voted as best goal of the tournament.<ref name="eltiempo.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.eltiempo.com/deportes/futbol/ARTICULO-WEB-NEW_NOTA_INTERIOR-12934901.html|title=Noticias Principales de Colombia y el Mundo – El Tiempo|first=Casa Editorial El|last=Tiempo|website=El Tiempo}}</ref>

===Olympics Squad===
Quintero expressed great interest in representing Colombia in 2016 for the [[Football at the 2016 Summer Olympics|Olympics in Brazil]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elespectador.com/deportes/futbolcolombiano/quintero-quiere-ser-clave-sub-23-busca-un-cupo-los-olim-articulo-607440|title=Quintero quiere ser clave para la sub-23 que busca un cupo a los Olímpicos – ELESPECTADOR.COM|date=23 December 2015|access-date=25 December 2015|archive-date=25 December 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151225020048/http://www.elespectador.com/deportes/futbolcolombiano/quintero-quiere-ser-clave-sub-23-busca-un-cupo-los-olim-articulo-607440|url-status=live}}</ref>

In February 2016, Quintero was called up to play back to back friendlies against [[Honduras national under-23 football team|Honduras]]. He made his debut in the first match resulting in a 1–1 draw. Days later in the second match, he scored with a free kick in a 2–2 draw.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.futbolred.com/seleccion-colombia/resultado-partido-amistoso-colombia-y-honduras+16522468|title=Colombia Sub-23 volvió a empatar con Honduras: 2–2 en EE. UU.|first=Casa Editorial El|last=Tiempo|website=futbolred.com|access-date=28 February 2016|archive-date=4 March 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304083115/http://m.futbolred.com/seleccion-colombia/resultado-partido-amistoso-colombia-y-honduras+16522468|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Senior===
In 2012, Quintero was called for the [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|2014 FIFA World Cup qualifiers]] against [[Peru national football team|Peru]] and [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador]], without making an appearance. He made his international debut in a friendly match against [[Cameroon national football team|Cameroon]] later in the same year.

====2014 World Cup and Friendlies====
On 2 June 2014, Quintero was named in Colombia's 23-man squad for the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]] and assigned the number 20 shirt.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://msn.foxsports.com/soccer/story/recovering-falcao-left-off-colombia-s-final-23-player-world-cup-roster-060214|title=Recovering Falcao left off Colombia's final 23-player World Cup roster|date=2 June 2014|access-date=16 June 2014|work=Fox Sports|archive-date=13 June 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140613070523/http://msn.foxsports.com/soccer/story/recovering-falcao-left-off-colombia-s-final-23-player-world-cup-roster-060214|url-status=live}}</ref>
He made his World Cup debut against [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast]] in the group stage, coming on for [[Victor Ibarbo]] in the 53rd minute, and scored his first international goal to give the 2–1 win for ''Los Cafeteros''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/25285057|title=Colombia 2–1 Ivory Coast|date=19 June 2014|access-date=20 June 2014|website=BBC Sport|archive-date=20 June 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140620015941/http://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/25285057|url-status=live}}</ref>

In May 2018, in a friendly against France at the [[Parc des Princes]], Quintero scored the winning goal for Colombia, a penalty, in a 3–2 victory.<ref>{{Cite web |date=23 March 2018 |title=Por primera vez Colombia conquistó Francia: remontó 3-2 en París con el regreso al gol de la dupla James-Falcao |url=https://www.tudn.com/futbol/por-primera-vez-colombia-conquisto-francia-remonto-3-2-en-paris-con-el-regreso-al-gol-de-la-dupla-james-falcao |access-date=2024-12-21 |website=TUDN.com |language=es |archive-date=21 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241221063225/https://www.tudn.com/futbol/por-primera-vez-colombia-conquisto-francia-remonto-3-2-en-paris-con-el-regreso-al-gol-de-la-dupla-james-falcao |url-status=live }}</ref>

====2018 World Cup====
In May 2018, he was named in Colombia's preliminary 35 man [[Colombia national football team|squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018 World Cup]] in [[Russia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/amp/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb|title=Revealed: Every World Cup 2018 squad – Final 23-man lists|website=goal.com|publisher=Goal|date=4 June 2018|access-date=5 April 2020|archive-date=27 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190327101310/https://www.goal.com/en-gb/amp/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb|url-status=live}}</ref> On 19 June 2018, he scored in the opening game against [[Japan national football team|Japan]] with a free kick under the wall to tie the match 1–1 that ended in a 2–1 defeat. On 24 June 2018, Quintero played 73 minutes in Colombia's 3–0 victory over [[Poland national football team|Poland]] and assisted [[Radamel Falcao]]'s goal. Four days later on 28 June 2018, he played 90 minutes of Colombia's final game in the group stage against Senegal and provided the winning assist to Yerry Mina's goal off of a corner kick to secure first place in group H. On 3 July 2018, he played 88 minutes in the round of 16 game against [[England national football team|England]], as Colombia lost on penalties. His goal against Japan was voted the second best goal of the tournament, after [[Benjamin Pavard]]'s goal against [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44958821|title=Benjamin Pavard wins FIFA vote|work=BBC Sport|access-date=30 May 2021|archive-date=2 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210602225411/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44958821|url-status=live}}</ref>

==Style of play==
{{Quote box | width=30% | align=left| quote="Colombia’s Juan Quintero was exceptional. He could go on to become a player on a par with [[Lionel Messi]]. The composure he displayed was unbelievable for such a young player. Without a doubt he will go on to become one of the stars of the game."|source=<small>Former footballer [[Kubilay Türkyilmaz]]'s view on Quintero from the 2013 U-20 FIFA World Cup.<ref name="ReferenceA"/></small>}}

Quintero is well known for his playmaking, unpredictable creativity, and ball control.<ref name=":1">{{Cite news |last=James |first=Stuart |date=2014-07-02 |title=Colombia's other No10, Juan Fernando Quintero, is a star in the making |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/blog/2014/jul/02/juan-fernando-quintero-colombia-playmaker-world-cup-2014?utm_source=chatgpt.com |access-date=2024-12-21 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref>{{AI-retrieved source|date=March 2026|checked=no}}<ref>{{Cite web |last=Marshall |first=Euan |date=2013-01-12 |title=The young ones: An eye on the South America Under-20s Championship |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/south-america-under-20s-championship-preview-1531155 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140427005906/https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/south-america-under-20s-championship-preview-1531155 |archive-date=27 April 2014 |access-date=2024-12-21 |website=The Mirror |language=en}}</ref> He is also known for his powerful long range shot and set-pieces, and he has used this ability to deliver precise crosses, passes, and score many free-kicks throughout his career.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Colasimone |first=Dan |date=2 July 2013 |title=Juan Fernando Quintero: All You Need to Know About Colombia's Next Star |url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/1691256-juan-fernando-quintero-all-you-need-to-know-about-colombias-next-star |access-date=2024-12-21 |website=Bleacher Report |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Juan Quintero Football Statistics |url=http://www.whoscored.com/Players/118155/ |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131005063031/http://www.whoscored.com/Players/118155/ |archive-date=5 October 2013 |access-date= |publisher=WhoScored.com}}</ref><ref name="fifa.com" />

Due to his small stature, Quintero naturally has a lower center of gravity, allowing him to have higher balance and agility, similar to that of [[Lionel Messi]] and [[Diego Maradona]].<ref name="fifa.com"/> However, Quintero does not possess the quickness and balanced weak foot that the aforementioned players had; and at times Quintero has been criticized for being overweight.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |last=Picón |first=Jorge C. |date=2018-06-25 |title=Quintero: quality and vision - in the mould of James Rodríguez |url=https://en.as.com/en/2018/06/25/soccer/1529921071_087252.html |access-date=2024-12-21 |website=AS USA |language=en-us |archive-date=25 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241225235402/https://en.as.com/en/2018/06/25/soccer/1529921071_087252.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2018-02-07 |title=Quintero: "No soy gordo, soy nalgón" |url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/copa-libertadores/2018/02/07/5a7aba15e5fdeae44e8b457d.html |access-date=2024-12-21 |website=Marca.com |language=es |archive-date=14 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240414195908/https://www.marca.com/futbol/copa-libertadores/2018/02/07/5a7aba15e5fdeae44e8b457d.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=2023-08-05 |title=Juanfer Quintero: su primera práctica con el plantel de Racing y los kilos que debe bajar |url=https://www.ole.com.ar/futbol-primera/racing-juanfer-quintero-gago_0_AU1bAWA53X.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230805214006/https://www.ole.com.ar/futbol-primera/racing-juanfer-quintero-gago_0_AU1bAWA53X.html |archive-date=5 August 2023 |access-date=2024-12-21 |website=Olé |language=es-AR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=2023-03-27 |title=Juan Fernando Quintero sobre su estado físico: "Ya pasó esa etapa pecar de ignorante" |url=https://www.semana.com/deportes/articulo/juan-fernando-quintero-sobre-su-estado-fisico-ya-paso-esa-etapa-pecar-de-ignorante/202337/ |access-date=2024-12-21 |website=Semana.com |language=spanish |archive-date=5 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230605105249/https://www.semana.com/deportes/articulo/juan-fernando-quintero-sobre-su-estado-fisico-ya-paso-esa-etapa-pecar-de-ignorante/202337/ |url-status=live }}</ref> His lack of quickness has also drawn comparisons to [[James Rodríguez]], due to the fact that they have lacked pace throughout their careers and both play in the #10 role.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" />

Quintero states that as a child his main inspiration was Brazilian legend [[Rivaldo]].<ref>{{cite web |date=1 November 2013 |title=Juan Fernando Quintero, el irreverente colombiano admirador de Rivaldo |url=http://www.vanguardia.com/deportes/futbol-internacional/232096-juan-fernando-quintero-el-irreverente-colombiano-admirador-de-r |website=vanguardia.com |access-date=6 November 2013 |archive-date=12 March 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140312171530/http://www.vanguardia.com/deportes/futbol-internacional/232096-juan-fernando-quintero-el-irreverente-colombiano-admirador-de-r |url-status=live }}</ref>

